question_evaluations.answer: Asynchronous programming means running parallel programming. Synchronous programming is running sequentially. Async / Await key word enables asynchronous programming. Based on requirements I would select language.

weaknesses: The answer lacks technical accuracy, is extremely brief, and fails to provide any meaningful comparison between Python and Node.js, or discuss how to decide which one to use in a given project, which are the core components of the question.
